Reasoning: The paper deals with developing an automatic visual recognition system using convolutional neural networks to read the results from the Paper Analytical Devices (PADs) for detecting falsified pharmaceuticals. This involves image processing, computer vision, and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the computer science sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV), cryptography and security (cs.CR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
